title: ApeFest Attendees Report Experiencing Eye Pain, Yuga Labs Says 'Less Than 1%' Affected
description: Yuga Labs told Decrypt that of the 2,250 ApeFest attendees, it has only been in direct contact with 15 people who claim to have been affected.

title: Major crypto scam is being investigated by authorities in Himachal Pradesh
description: In a significant crackdown on high-profile cryptocurrency fraud, the Special Investigation Team (SIT) in Himachal Pradesh has made substantial headway, detaining eight individuals, including four police officers, in connection with a colossal Rs 2,500 crore ($300.45 million) scam that has been unraveling since 2018. title: UKRI Invests £117 Million in AI Doctoral Training
description: UK Research and Innovation (UKRI) has allocated a substantial £117 million in funding for the establishment of 12 centres for doctoral training (CDTs) in the field of artificial intelligence (AI). title: Binance to Halt TOMO Deposits and Withdrawals on November 20
description:
Binance today disclosed that it would suspend deposits and withdrawals of TOMO on its platform and payment channels as the project’s team undergoes a rebranding.  Indeed, TomoChain on November 1 announced it would rebrand to Viction. As a result, the project’s ticker will also change from TOMO to VIC to symbolize the newly adopted name.  […]
